en_58164_0	Canada says that a full delegation will not be  deployed to participate in the Commonwealth Summit held in Sri Lanka.
en_58164_1	A Canadian Foreign Affairs Department spokeswoman said that the reason for this was the human rights problems prevalent in Sri Lanka.
en_58164_2	But she also said that Canada was on the watch about the Summit affairs.
en_58164_3	However by now several countries have already stated that they would participate in the Commonwealth Summit due to be held in Sri Lanka.
en_58164_4	Commonwealth Secretary General Kamalesh Sharma too said that the Commonwealth of  Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM) would definitely be held in Sri Lanka in November.
en_58164_5	Cabinet spokesman Minister Keheliya Rambukwella expressed the following view recently with regard to the CHOGM.
